      "id": 361489,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The step-growth polymer nylon 6 is prepared from caprolactam. The reaction involves initial reaction of caprolactam with water to give an intermediate open-chain amino acid, followed by heating to form the polymer. Propose mechanisms for both steps, and show the structure of nylon 6.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa0VYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--74f76058badf9a0806584bcc9894e3833d264ec1/OChem_21_EC_042.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of caprolactam comprises of a seven-membered ring containing a carbonyl group attached to an N H group.\">",
